# Changelog - xcesppkg

## 0.0.21

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.17: `ProcClient::handleAck()` fix — `ACK CMD=RESET`
  no longer clears `pendingAttrs_`; fixes attr-level diff regression where all
  objects were redeployed on every config commit instead of only changed ones

## 0.0.20

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.22: `CandidateConfig::createNode()` is now idempotent
  — navigating to an existing node in `conf !` mode no longer prints a
  spurious error

## 0.0.19

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.16: attr-level diff in `ProcClient::deployObjects()`
  — on config commit only objects with changed INI attributes are redeployed;
  unchanged objects are silently skipped

## 0.0.18

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.9: `IpCmd::exec()` and `IpCmd::run()` use
  `fork()+exec()` with ambient `CAP_NET_ADMIN`+`CAP_SYS_ADMIN` instead of
  `popen()`/`system()` — fixes VRF and interface creation failing with
  `RTNETLINK answers: Operation not permitted` because file capabilities on
  xcespproc were dropped when exec'ing the unprivileged `ip(8)` binary

## 0.0.17

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.15: `ProcClient::deployObjects()` fixes dual-proc
  deployment race (pending objects now cancelled before ACK can promote them);
  `XCespServer` honours `LOG_CONSOLE_LEVEL` INI key to suppress DEBUG noise

## 0.0.16

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.8: `RtrVrfPObj::applyConfig()` uses
  `IpCmd::exec(cmd, errOut)` to log VRF creation failures at WARNING;
  `monitorVrf()` re-creates missing VRF devices (matching router namespace
  re-creation pattern)

## 0.0.15

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.7: `IpCmd::createNetns()` creates network
  namespaces via `fork()+unshare(CLONE_NEWNET)+mount(MS_BIND)`, bypassing
  `ip netns add`'s `mount --make-shared /run/netns` step that fails for
  non-root processes even with `CAP_SYS_ADMIN`
- `xcesp-activate`: pre-creates `/run/netns` owned by xcesp so xcespproc
  can write namespace bind-files without root privileges

## 0.0.14

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.6: `IpCmd::exec(cmd, output)` overload captures
  stderr; `RtrRouterPObj` now logs the exact `ip netns add` failure message
  at WARNING level when namespace creation or re-creation fails

## 0.0.13

- `cfg/xcespwdog.ini`: enable `[process.3]` — xcespproc instance 2
  (affinity 2); was commented out, causing affinity-2 objects (e.g.
  `router ra`) to fall back to xcespproc-1 instead of running on their
  own dedicated process instance

## 0.0.12

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.14: hook validation now also runs on startup
  config (non-fatal — logs WARNING); invalid configs that pre-date hooks
  are now surfaced at server startup rather than silently persisting

## 0.0.11

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.5: `router.validate.py` affinity conflict check
- makefile: flatten `*.validate.py` hooks from plugin schema dirs
  (`on-rtr/`, `on-pw/`, `on-xc/`) to top-level `schema/` so xcespserver
  can find them via its single schemaDir

## 0.0.10

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.21: `--whole-archive` fix — `RtrRouter`, `RtrVrf`,
  `RtrInterface`, `RtrVlan`, `RtrStaticRoute` process objects now correctly
  registered at runtime (linker was silently dropping static initialisers)
- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.4: remove reserved `attr name` from
  `address.schema` (eliminates WARNING at server startup)

## 0.0.9

- `xcesp-activate`: create `/run/xcesp` with correct ownership/permissions on
  every invocation — `/run` is tmpfs and is cleared on reboot; `RuntimeDirectory=`
  in the systemd unit covers the managed-service path, but manual invocations
  (direct `sudo xcesp-activate`, xcesptest `start.sh`) had no fallback, causing
  xcespserver to fail binding its UDS control socket `/run/xcesp/ctrl.sock`

## 0.0.8

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.13, xcespcli 0.0.21, xcespwdog 0.0.6
- xcespschema 0.0.5: case-insensitive keywords, `_boolean` built-in type,
  `attr name` reserved, schema cross-reference validation (`validateRefs()`)
- xcespconfig 0.0.6: child-ref constraint validation in `validate()`,
  Python hook validation (`validateHooks()`), skip auto-injected `name`
  in validation, IOS bool uses `isUseNoType()` (not `isBoolType()`)
- xcespserver 0.0.13: schema validation now fatal (rejects config on error),
  Python hook validation added to `applyNewConfig()`
- xcespcli 0.0.21: commit pre-validates before sending to server, case-insensitive
  command dispatch, enum canonicalization, IOS bool display fix

## 0.0.7

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.12: startup config loading now uses schema-based
  disambiguation, fixing `shutdown` (single-token bool) being misclassified
  as a child block opener — xcespserver no longer fails to start when the
  config contains bare bool attributes like `shutdown`

## 0.0.6

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.20: `config !` temporarily enables auto-create for
  the config session; `end` restores prior behaviour

## 0.0.5

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.19: `--no-create` is now the default (require `'!'` to
  create nodes); `--create` flag enables auto-creation without `'!'`

## 0.0.4

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.18 with fix for `show running` / `show candidate`
  displaying `shutdown false` instead of `no shutdown` at root navigation level

## 0.0.3

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.17 with `TerminalParams` CLI flags:
  `-v`/`--verbose <0-5>`, `-l`/`--lines <N>`, `-t`/`--timeout <N>`,
  `--no-create`/`--create`; all map directly to `CliSession::terminalParams()`
  at startup

## 0.0.2

- Bundles xcespschema 0.0.4, xcespserver 0.0.11, xcespcli 0.0.16 with fixes for:
  - Commit rejection when config contains address sub-nodes (xcespserver 0.0.11)
  - `show candidate` displaying `shutdown false` instead of `no shutdown` (xcespcli 0.0.16)
  - `?`/TAB completion and navigation now restricted to valid node types at each
    path depth (root: domain, router only) (xcespcli 0.0.16 + xcespschema 0.0.4)
  - After `discard`, navigation path auto-reset to root if it no longer exists (xcespcli 0.0.16)
  - `TerminalParams` structure added to xcespcli (xcespcli 0.0.16)

## 0.0.1

- Initial release: tarball-based installer for XCESP
- Bundles xcespserver, xcespcli, xcespproc, xcespwdog binaries
- Bundles schema, Python rules (worker + config-to-objects + status-to-global),
  and xcesppy Python client library
- install.sh: creates xcesp system user/group, installs binaries to /usr/bin,
  sets cap_net_admin,cap_sys_admin=ep on xcespproc, installs config templates
  to /var/xcesp/cfg (non-destructive — existing files are not overwritten),
  creates Python venv at /var/xcesp/venv, installs systemd service xcesp.service
